formatted_address: 63 Jurong West Central 3, #03-52/52A Jurong Point, Singapore 648331
name: Starbucks - Jurong Point

reviews.text: Cake was good , but the cashier was speaking too fast . He seemed friendly but a bit impatient, which was understandable as there was a long line

This is a surprisingly vibey Starbucks! It’s in the middle of the mall, but it’s a nice place to sit. They have wifi and comfortable chairs, lots of tables.
The coffee was a bit worse than normal for Starbucks, but okay.
They were really friendly!

We recently visited Starbucks at Jurong Point Mall, and as always, I had to get my favorite Java Chip Frappuccino. The place was great cozy, comfortable, and perfect for a quick break. I really enjoyed the ambiance, and the service was prompt.

It’s definitely one of those places I’ll keep coming back to

Quite and comfortable place to stay for studying or meeting friends.
Very big space, got outdoor seatings and indoor.
However extremely slow service, too much ordering from the delivery and somehow the order was mixed up.

Located at Level 3, Jurong Point new wing.

Compliements to the Lady Staff at Cashier taking my order who was friendly, patient and helpful during my visit at about 1720H.

Place is Crowded barely any seats left for Crowds more than 2 persons.

F&B orders were prompt and accurate.
